    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and a very generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potato is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
